RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEGEND'S SONG trailed the field up the backstretch and around the turn, began a bid from the four path passing the quarter pole and gained ground quickly to pull clear late. WICKED SAUCY led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and was caught in late stretch after drifting mildly in the final furlong. GINGER SPARKLE raced off the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and improved position in the lane. ANGELIC STORM stumbled leaving the gate, recovered to stalk the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the four path coming around the turn and faded in the stretch. TOOSWEETFORME raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the turn in the three path and showed no kick. TEA'S DREAM tracked the pace setter between horses up the backstretch, began to drop back while racing in the two path around the turn and tired further from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 90. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since January 8 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WAR CROSS raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid coming around the far turn, was fanned out to the five path entering the stretch and kicked clear in the final furlong. CUZ saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, dueled from the four path coming around the far turn, swung wide into the stretch, could not go with the winner late and chased that rival home. CANDY COVE led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled around the far bend, still in the two path, and was outkicked in the stretch. ARIES REIGNS raced in the two path early, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and tired from there. ODDS ON reared up tremendously at the break, trailed throughout and was declared a non starter. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT HORSE SIX, ODDS ON, DID NOT HAVE A FAIR BEGINNING AND WAS DECLARED A NON STARTER.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE SEPTEMBER 8. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since January 8 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSY OF COURSE saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the far turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and drew off to the wire. BEAUTIFUL TIZ raced in the two path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the second bend in the four path and chased the winner home in the lane. OUR FANTASY saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the far bend, was outkicked in the stretch and kept on to the wire. MONIQUES DAREDEVIL raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn and flattened out in the stretch. SHE B GLAMOROUS raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and showed no kick. LOOK UP TO HEAVEN led the way from the two path around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the second bend and faded in the lane. DIXIELAND DANCER trailed the field the entire way around the oval, saved ground around the second turn and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 1 1/16M Turf CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Hav e Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRALINE'S CAT saved ground around the first turn, led the field on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second bend, drifted out in upper stretch, coming into close contact with MASTER SERGEANT, veered in sharply from there to bump with THE SWAYZE EXPRESS near the sixteenth pole and kicked clear late. CORE FACTOR raced in the two path around the first bend, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the four path, drifted in and bumped with THE SWAYZE EXPRESS in upper stretch and chased the winner home in the lane. THE SWAYZE EXPRESS saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path, bumped with CORE FACTOR and was forced in in upper stretch, gained ground, was bumped hard and took up sharply when PRALINE'S CAT veered into his lane near the wire and kept on from there. MASTER SERGEANT saved ground around the first bend, tracked the leader between horses up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path, raced in tight quarters with PRALINE'S CAT in upper stretch and kept on to the finish. EL BUFFALO raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn and finished evenly. DAD'S ON A ROLL saved ground early, raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the four path and never threatened. CHIEF BULLET raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far turn and made no bid. FOREVER SAUCY raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, navigated the far bend still in the three path and tired in the stretch. GO GO GREEN raced in the two path around the first bend, settled off the pace between horses for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn and was empty in the lane. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO LATE STRETCH. THE RIDER OF HORSE FIVE, THE SWAYZE EXPRESS, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE ONE, PRALINE'S CAT, IN LATE STRETCH. THE TRAINER OF HORSE FIVE, THE SWAYZEE EXPRESS, CLAIMED FOUR AGAINST HORSE FOUR, CORE FACTOR, IN UPPER STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, HORSE ONE, PRALINES CAT, WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED THIRD FOR INTERFERENCE WITH HORSE FIVE, THE SWAYZEE EXPRESS IN LATE STRETCH.
